cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on the development of a semantic segmentation network to label temporary works and ESAs in railway construction using VHR satellite images. This falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of DCNNs and attention cross entropy loss function in the proposed framework suggests the application of artificial intelligence techniques. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The use of DCNNs for semantic segmentation and training the network on VHR true color images indicates the application of machine learning. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics): The use of satellite images and Google Earth in the proposed framework suggests the application of graphics. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics): Although not directly related to robotics, the proposed framework can be useful in monitoring the progress of railway construction projects, which can be relevant to robotics applications in the construction industry.
